  <description type="morphology">Culms 45–150 cm. Leaf blades 24–50 cm × 4.8–14 mm. Inflorescences: peduncle of proximal spike 0.5–6.8 cm; proximal bract longer than inflorescence, 4.6–12 mm wide; pistillate spikes 3–5; the proximal 3.4–12 cm × 3.3–7 mm. Pistillate scales (including awn) 3.4–9.8 mm. Perigynia divergent to ascending, broadly obovoid, 2–3.9 × 1.8–2.8 mm, apex obtuse to truncate; beak 0.2–0.5 mm. Achenes not constricted. 2n = 66.</description>
